Usage: vcpe <command> [flags]

Commands:
  init      Initialize the vCPE state root
  build     Build or pull service images from a manifest
  push      Push service images from a manifest to their registries
  release   Stamp manifest, commit, tag, push git, then build and push images
  up        Bring up a deployment from a manifest
  plan      Show planned changes without applying
  down      Tear down a named deployment
  list      List known deployments
  manifest  Manage and discover manifest files
  status    Show control-plane status
  logs      Show operation timeline and deployment logs
  config    Show effective configuration
  state     Manage persisted control-plane state
  version   Print the vcpe version

Aliases:
  apply    alias for up
  destroy  alias for down (also requires --force)

Global flags:
  --state-root <path>  Override state root directory
  --config <path>      Config file path
  --socket <path>      Daemon socket path

Run `vcpe <command> --help` for command-specific help.
